<meta name=3D"DC.Description" content=3D"A Taylor series is a series expans=
ion of a function about a point. A one-dimensional Taylor series is an expa=
nsion of a real function f(x) about a point x=3Da is given by  (1)   If a=
=3D0, the expansion is known as a Maclaurin series. Taylor's theorem (actua=
lly discovered first by Gregory) states that any function satisfying certai=
n conditions can be expressed as a Taylor series. The Taylor (or more gener=
al) series of a function f(x) about a point a up to order n may be found us=
ing Series[f, {x,...">
