<div class=3D"entry-content">
<p>
A Taylor series is a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SeriesExpansi=
on.html">series expansion</a> of a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com=
/Function.html">function</a> about a point. A one-dimensional Taylor series
 is an expansion of a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/RealFunction=
.html">real function</a> <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/e=
quations/TaylorSeries/Inline1.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-hei=
ght:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"35" height=3D"21" alt=3D"f(x=
)"> about a point <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equation=
s/TaylorSeries/Inline2.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100=
%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"39" height=3D"21" alt=3D"x=3Da"> is=
 given by
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0" style=3D"padding-left: 50px">
