(1)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
If <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/TaylorSeries/=
Inline3.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100=
%" border=3D"0" width=3D"39" height=3D"21" alt=3D"a=3D0">, the expansion is=
 known as a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/MaclaurinSeries.html">=
Maclaurin
 series</a>.
</p>
<p>
<a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/TaylorsTheorem.html">Taylor's theo=
rem</a> (actually discovered first by Gregory) states that any function sat=
isfying certain conditions can be expressed
 as a Taylor series.
</p>
<p>
The Taylor (or more general) series of a function <img src=3D"https://mathw=
orld.wolfram.com/images/equations/TaylorSeries/Inline4.svg" class=3D"inline=
formula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"35"=
